        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 5. Miconia friedmaniorum Almeda & Umaña. A. Branch showing asymmetric leaf bases of most leaves. B. Flowering branch showing deflexed posture of inflorescence. C. Flower. D. Infructescence. E. Floral bud with fused sepals that have ruptured. F. Longitudinal section of flower bud. G. Profile view of flower at anthesis. H. Flower at anthesis viewed from above. I. Petal. J. Stamen. All from R. Kriebel et al. 5461 (INB)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4814557/files/figure.png" .

